 rays favours a connection\nbetween neutrino filtered emitters and cosmic rays with a probability of\n$\\sim1.8\\times10^{-3}$ ($2.9\\sigma)$ after compensation for all the considered\ntrials. The neutrino filtered $\\gamma$-ray sources that make up the cosmic rays\nexcess are blazars of the high synchrotron peak type. More statistics is needed\nto further investigate these sources as candidate cosmic ray and neutrino\nemitters.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 18 Nov 2016 09:52:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 27 Feb 2017 16:27:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-04-12"}
